{
  /*
   * Production-build type-check config.
   *
   * `npm run build` runs `tsc -p tsconfig.build.json && vite build`. This
   * config extends the editor/test tsconfig but EXCLUDES test files and test
   * scaffolding, so a type slip in a *.test.ts (e.g. a vitest mock annotation)
   * can never block the shippable SPA (test files are never bundled anyway).
   * Test type-checking still happens via `npm test` (vitest), which uses the
   * base tsconfig.json that includes them.
   *
   * Why this exists: the storefront SPA must build on every fresh workshop box.
   * The old `tsc && vite build` type-checked all 48 test files as a build gate,
   * so one test-only error left `dist/` unbuilt and the Boutique/Atelier blank.
   */
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "exclude": [
    "src/stories/**",
    ".storybook/**",
    "src/**/*.test.ts",
    "src/**/*.test.tsx",
    "src/test-setup.ts"
  ]
}
